          "text": "Analyze the logic in `State.backspace` in @src/liblex.zig to see if I miss any logic. My intentions:\n\n- When user input \"backspace\", the State will remove the last span.\n- Because we use buffer_length to determine the buffer_effective length, there is no need to actually remove the span, descrease the buffer_length is enough.\n- When the length reduce pass the literal_index, it mean we go back tho Vietnamese processing, we must unset the index.\n- Am I missing something?\n\nDon't change any code. Just discuss with me about this function.",
